<Sect2 Id="OSFGDS.GDSSHA.div.30">
<Title>Remove Update Errors</Title>
<IndexTerm Id="OSFGDS.GDSSHA.indx.66">
<Primary>shadowing jobs</Primary>
<Secondary>errors</Secondary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm Id="OSFGDS.GDSSHA.indx.67">
<Primary><Literal>remove update errors</Literal> operation</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<Para>The <Literal>Remove Update Errors</Literal> operation removes an update error.
</Para>
<Para><?sml-need 3.5i><Literal>Mask sequence</Literal>
</Para>
<VariableList>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Mask 3</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Select option number 3
(see 
<!-- the chapter entitled "Logon to a DSA or to the Cache").-->
Chapter 7).
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Mask 13</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Select option number 8.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Mask 15</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Displays the update error.
</Para>
<Para>If <Literal>Remove Update Error</Literal> is set to <Literal>YES</Literal>, this update error is ignored by the
delta update process at the next activation time (otherwise, the
delta update process tries to resend the erroneous update operation to
the target DSA).
</Para>
<Para>To display the next update error, press
<Literal>&lt;Menu&gt;</Literal>, <Literal>&lt;Scroll Down&gt;</Literal>, or
<Literal>&lt;Return&gt;</Literal>. </Para>
<Para>Terminate the operation by pressing
<Literal>&lt;Del&gt;</Literal>. </Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
</VariableList>
<Para>Figure 10-27 shows a sample mask sequence that removes an update 
error for a shadowing job.  The update error is an attribute error, 
<Literal>33=Attribute missing</Literal>, which could occur if the object on the target 
DSA no longer contains the specified attribute because it has been removed. 
Administrator's selections are highlighted in bold.
